The Co-Prosperity Sphere | Page 112 | alternatehistory.com Search Everywhere Threads This forum This thread Search titles only By: Word Count: Search Advanced search… Recent threadmarks Chapter 633: Dr. 
Abraham Kaufmann and the Jewish Zionist Community inside the Co-Prosperity Sphere In the Empire of Manchukuo, Emperor Puyi was meeting with Dr. 
Abraham Kaufmann, a local Zionist, anticommunist leader from Harbin. 
Kaufmann had emigrated there in 1912 and had quickly become the shtadlan (community organizer) in many local Jewish organizations. 
During 1914 he organized the EKOPO society (Jewish Committee for the Help of War Victims) to assist some 200,000 First Great War refugees with shelter, food and medical care. 
In 1919 he became a Zionist leader in the Harbin Jewish community, and of overall Manchuria/ Manchukuo during the 1930ies. 
As a integrated part of Harbin Jewry cultural and political organizations, Kaufmann was variously the medical director of the Jewish hospital of Harbin, chairman of the Harbin's Jewish community, chairman of the Jewish National Fund and Keren Hayesod Zionist fundraising organizations, he was a board member of the World Zionist Organization and the Jewish Agency, chairman of the Jewish Zionist organization of China (later the Jewish Zionist organization of the Co-Prosperity Sphere), was president of the Hebrew Association of Harbin, chief editor of the Evreiskaya Zhizn ("Jewish Life" – Еврейская жизнь) weekly Jewish magazine in Russian in the Jewish Autonomous Oblast (from 1921 on) and chairman of the National Council of the Jews of Eastern Asia (Far East) since 1937, as well as the was also the head of the Far Eastern Jewish Council (FEJ – Национального Совета) which he helped found, and also the Vaad Haleumi (Ваад-Галеуми), both founded in 1937 with the encouragement of Japanese officials such as Colonel Norijiro Yasue and Captain Koreshige Inuzuka (the so called Japanese Jewish Experts). 
Their so called Fugu Plan saw Jews persecuted in Europe brought into the Co-Prosperity Sphere were they could use their (originating mainly from anti-Semite propaganda) believed expertise as doctors, scientists, lawyers and government leading members for the Japanese and their Coprospist ambitions. 
Major support for the new Jewish province also came from Yoshisuke Aikawa (or Gisuke Ayukawa) (鮎川 義介 Aikawa Yoshisuke, born on 6 November 1880, a Japanese entrepreneur, businessman, and politician, noteworthy as the founder and first president of the Nissan Zaibatsu (1931-1945), one of Japan's most powerful business conglomerates around the time of the Second Great War. 
Thanks to his support for Dr. 
Abraham Kaufmann, Nissan would gain access to the cast resources and marked in the Empire of Manchukuo and even dominate the Jewish province industry and economy uncontested. 
(the Jewish Amur Tiger, here switched around compared to that of the Coastal Provinces of the Primorsky Krai with nearly the same colors, then the Khabarovsk Krai or the Green Ukraine the later also incorporated into the Manchukuo Empire, the Aquamarine background represents the color of the vast Far eastern taiga, hills, meadows in the region) 
With the Japanese, Korean, Manchurian and Mengjiang Empire's push northwards during Hokushin-ron, they quickly captured the Soviet Union's Far Eastern Provinces, including the Jewish Autonomous Oblast (JAO). 
The JAO's Jewish population made up between 17,000 and 20,000 people, or around 16% of the total population between 1937 to 1939. 
However with the Axis Central Powers politics and later their advance during the Eastern Crusade and their support and use of Jewish populations and collaborators along their invasion, Stalin ordered Jews to be deported to Siberia and the Far East. 
By the 1940ies the Jewish population of the region had already reached 46,000 to 50,000 or 25 percent of the entire population. 
And when the Co-Prosperity Sphere invaded in 1941, the Jews inside the JAO for the first time made up 94,000 to 102,000 or a little over 50 percent of the entire population. 
Left to govern themselves Manchurian Emperor Puyi as well as Colonel Norijiro Yasue and Captain Koreshige Inuzuka tried to implement their Fugu Plan finally to full extent and expelled all Russians from the Region, while White Ukrainians were allowed to remain among other Tungusic peoples (who alongside the Han Chinese, were all declared to be Manchu inside the Empire of Manchuria to boost the Manchurian's numbers). 
Because of his popularity and influence, Dr. 
Kaufmann was quickly appointed to be the Governor of the Jewish Province of Manchuria. 
However Puyi hoped that with great Jewish autonomy and provincial independence more Jews would be willing to help out in the government of the rest of his Empire, as well as help with some financial projects like the industrialization, the building of roads, bridges, railroads and even channels. 
While Dr. 
Kaufmann was willing to help the Manchurian and the Japanese for their help and protection, he also argued that he had to focus most Jewish attention on the build up of modern structures like schools, hospitals and even the own growing industries of the Jewish Province, that would also benefit the Manchurian Empire, the Japanese Empire and the overall Co-Prosperity Sphere, before he could spare and divide the finally strong and growing Jewish community and it's modernisation.   
